args: Hiking, hiking, I'm oh-a-so-a liking\nbeing out a-hiking, la-de-dah-de-doo!
Ahhh! Smell that fresh mountain air!\n...Huh?
Three thousand fifty-six!\nThree thousand fifty-seven!\nThree thousand fifty-eight!
It's Celliera! She's doing jump squats...\nand it looks like she means business!
Wait, she's got a tent. Did she come here\nto climb the mountain, too?
She doesn't strike me as a nature buff.\nMaybe she's out here to train?
She must be taking on some special foe\nif she's secluding herself in the mountains\nlike this.
Well, let's ask her and find out.
Hoo-rah! Four thousand!\nNext, I'm going to—
Whatcha doing all that training for?\nTrying to overcome your eternal rival\nor something?
Ah. You saw that, did you?
I'm a bit embarrassed by this, but if you\nalready saw me, I suppose I have no\nchoice but honesty...
I've been training out here for the sake of\nmy pride as a knight's armsmaster.
As someone who trains others, I, too, must\nalways be diligent in my own training.\nThis is what I mean by ＂pride.＂
Thus, from time to time, I come up into the\nmountains far from the eyes of others in\norder to hone my own body and mind.
That's a really great attitude, Celliera.\nEr, but why would you be embarrassed\nabout that?
Because doing it in front of people makes\nit seem as though I'm showing off.
How should I put this... It's a bit\nundignified to see one's teacher exerting\nherself in such a manner.
Woooow! You're more vain than I thought!
I don't think it's undignified at all. In fact,\nI think you should show this side to people\nmore often.
It's great to see someone working\nhard. People who put a lot of effort into\nthings are trustworthy, after all.
If everyone knew how hard you work to\nbetter yourself, I'm sure they'd trust you\neven more.
At the very least, knowing how hard you\nwork makes me personally feel even more\nstrongly that—
Stop! Don't say anything else!\n...This is embarrassing.
Aaaah ha ha! Your face is bright red!
Oh, and speaking of bright red,\nthe sun's about to do its setting thing.
Guess we should be getting back down the\nmountain. You too, Celliera.
I'm so thirsty, I can't sleep. Huh?\nThat light...
I'm pretty sure that's her room.
Oh, hello there, {player_name}.\nDo you need something?
What are you doing up so late, Celliera?
Working on my records of all the people in\nthe castle.
What the condition of their health is like,\nanything I saw while fighting with them...\nThat sort of thing.
Keeping a detailed record of such things\ncan come in handy when helping people\ntrain and better themselves.
Although, I tend to write too much, so it\nalways keeps me up well into the night.
Now that I look closely, you've got a lot of\nbooks here. Are they all on medicine and\nmartial arts?
Yes. All reference materials for when\nI'm thinking about intensive training.
You hone your body during the day\nand your mind at night. You're really\npassionate about teaching people, huh?
Helping people grow is my joy.
Nothing can top the swell of pride I feel\nwhen I help someone succeed.
That's why I chose my profession of\nknight's armsmaster.
You know? I'm quite glad that I came to\nthe Halidom.
The people in this castle are the cream of\na very distinguished crop, and I'm certain\neach one will become noteworthy.
I can't help but be excited when I think\nI might be able to play some small role\nin that eventuality.
I know so. And as such, I'd like to train you\nwith even more fervor!
Heh. Sounds like I might regret that.\nBut by all means, please do so.
